item.description: Supported Terraform Commands # Most terraform commands are supported. A (Q) means it is a queueable command. apply(Q) console destroy(Q) fmt force-unlock(Q) get graph import(Q) init(Q) output plan providers providers lock refresh(Q) state list state mv(Q) state pull state push(Q) state replace-provider(Q) state rm(Q) state show show taint(Q) untaint(Q) validate Ensure terraform flags follow a double dash: etok apply -- -auto-approve
Additional Commands # sh(Q) - run shell or arbitrary command in workspace
